Hi, my name is Flynn!  I'm a 10yr old handsome boy waiting for my forever home!Let's get the obvious out of the way...I have funny looking ears!  I'm an American Curl and that is the way my ears come!  They give me character, don't you think?I'm very sweet, friendly and affectionate, and love to be petted head to tail.  I especially like having the sides of my neck scratched!  I will rub against you and purr in appreciation, and I often pace to help you find the best spot to pet me!I don't mind being held and will sit nicely in your arms as you carry me around, but I really perk up when you hold me by a window.  Hopefully my new home will have a nice window perch for me!  I'm not really a lap cat, at least not at the shelter.  As soon as the volunteer sat down I wanted to get up and explore!I am FIV+ (the kitty version of HIV in people).  I will need to be indoor only, and either an only cat or in a home with other FIV+ kitties.  FIV+ kitties can live just as long as other kitties!  I also have chronic otitis...basically I keep getting an infection in my outer ear canal.  I also have a broken canine tooth and some gingival recession.  I recently had dental surgery on 8/22/15.  I may require specialized care in the future.  The officers and veterinarians at the shelter will be happy to answer any questions when you come visit me!I am litter box trained, neutered, current on my vaccinations, and micro chipped!If you would like to meet me in person and get to know me better, you can find me at the King County Pet Adoption Center in Kent, located at 21615 64th Ave S.  Please come and see me today...I can't wait to meet you!  We just might make the purr-fect family!When you do come visit me, please make sure to reference my ID #A472340.  See you soon!
